				&lt;filtering&gt;true&lt;/filtering&gt;
			&lt;/resource&gt;
		&lt;/resources&gt;

Setting this to false fixes the issue. I still need to find a way to make it work with filtering enabled so I&#39;ll try to figure it out. There are some clues in other questions/answers like https://stackoverflow.com/questions/14327003/wrong-encoding-after-activating-resource-filtering. Thanks.

